de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.controller.datageneration
Class Facet

java.lang.Object
  de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.controller.datageneration.Facet

public class Facet
extends java.lang.Object

This class represents a single facet. The difference to MetaAttribute is that this one is ready to get serialized into an XML file. MetaAttribute class is not designed to do that. The keyword here is separation of affairs.

getValue

public final java.lang.String getValue()
gets the value of this facet. Notice, at any time there's only one value returned. This is because all values are gathered to one single value and then it is returned.

Example
Suppose you've generated values to facet author and there is multipleValues? enabled. As a result of these settings you could get the following:
"Portman, Moore, Simpson"

But in the data structure these values are still separate.

Returns:
gets the generated value
